g.text: an extension point for stripe skipping as well as specializations of the meta-knowledge tag
The header for Nodes allows an arbitrary number of <meta> elements.
Logical entailments accept the header pattern common to Nodes.
The if of an implication rule (<Implies>) containing the Premise(s), also known
an extension point for stripe skipping as well as specializations of the if tag name in entailments.
The then of an implication rule (<Implies>) containing the conclusion, also
an extension point for stripe skipping as well as specializations of the then tag name in entailments.
In the normal-form serialization, the if and then of a proof-theoretic entailment must occur canonical order.
